  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2023-10-24",
    "date": "2024-01-24T19:47:22Z",
    "text": "Expanding Health Care Options for First Responders Act\n\nThis bill establishes a Medicare buy-in option for certain qualifying first responders.\n\nSpecifically, the bill allows first responders aged 50 to 64 to enroll in Medicare if they are retired or otherwise separated from service due to a disability. The Centers for Medicare & Medicaid Services (CMS) must determine enrollment periods and set premiums for the buy-in option established under the bill, in accordance with specified requirements. The CMS must also award grants to states and nonprofit organizations for outreach and enrollment activities relating to the buy-in option."
  },
